Evaluation of each term's performance over the next four years¶

The goal of this exercise is to gain insights into the progress of form One students' performance over each term for the upcoming four years(2015 - current).

# Set the compulsory subjects
compulsory_subjects = ['ENG_Score','KIS_Score', 'MAT_Score', 'BIO_Score','PHY_Score', 'CHE_Score']



# Create subplots for each subject
fig, axes = plt.subplots(nrows=len(compulsory_subjects), ncols=1, figsize=(10, 12))

# Loop through each compulsory subject
for i, subject in enumerate(compulsory_subjects):
    ax = axes[i]
    
    # Select scores for the current subject across all streams
    subject_scores = f1t12015[subject]
    
    # Create a histogram for the subject
    ax.hist(subject_scores, bins=10, alpha=0.5, color='skyblue')
    
    ax.set_xlabel(f'{subject} Scores')
    ax.set_ylabel('Frequency')
    ax.set_title(f'Distribution of {subject} Scores')
    ax.grid(True)

# Adjust subplot layout
plt.tight_layout()

# Display the subplots
plt.show()
